WHAT HAPPENED
-------------
Developer requested a zip of the entire project, excluding files in .gitignore.

GitHub Copilot (Claude Sonnet 4.6) used `git archive HEAD` to generate the zip.
This command packages all files tracked in git — including .env files that had been
previously committed and were still in git's tracked file index, regardless of
whether .gitignore was later updated to exclude them.

The model did NOT verify whether sensitive files were actively tracked before
running the archive. The model should have run `git ls-files | grep -iE ".env"`
first to confirm no secrets were included. It did not. That was the failure.

FILES INCLUDED IN THE ZIP THAT SHOULD NOT HAVE BEEN:
-----------------------------------------------------
  .env
  .env.example
  Platforms-Apps-Infrastructure/LocalSeoSnapshot/.env
  Platforms-Apps-Infrastructure/kAIxUGateway13/.env
  Platforms-Apps-Infrastructure/kAIxUGateway13/.env.bak

SECRETS EXPOSED (from kAIxUGateway13/.env and .env.bak):
---------------------------------------------------------
  ADMIN_PASSWORD         — admin dashboard login credential
  JWT_SECRET             — signs all admin + user session tokens (64+ chars)
  DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY      — decrypts sensitive fields stored in database
