ROOT CAUSE
----------
The .env files were committed to git at some point before .gitignore rules were
hardened. Once a file is tracked by git, .gitignore no longer excludes it from
git archive or any git operation — .gitignore only prevents UNTRACKED files from
being added. The model executed the archive without auditing tracked files first.

LESSON / RULE GOING FORWARD
----------------------------
Before running any git archive, zip, or export command:
  ALWAYS run: git ls-files | grep -iE "\.env|secret|key|token|credential"
  If ANY sensitive files are tracked, STOP and untrack them first.

